<p>1. How did the Prophet ﷺ raise his hands for the opening takbeer?<br>
A. To the waist, palms facing down<br>
B. Above the head, fingers tightly closed<br>
C. To the chest level, fingers spread wide<br>
D. To the shoulders or parallel to the earlobes, fingers natural</p>

<p>2. Ahmad says “Allāhu Akbar” at the start of the prayer but does not raise his hands at all during the opening takbeer. Which statement is most accurate?<br>
A. His prayer is invalid and he must repeat it.<br>
B. His prayer is valid, but he is sinful for leaving the raising of the hands.<br>
C. His prayer is valid, but he misses out on some reward by leaving sunnah.<br>
D. His prayer is valid, and he neither gains nor loses any reward by leaving this action.</p>

<p>3. If someone is new to Islam and does not yet know how to recite al-Fatihah in Arabic, what should he do while standing in prayer?<br>
A. Stand silently and wait for about 25–30 seconds.<br>
B. Go immediately into rukoo‘ without saying anything.<br>
C. Recite the translation of al-Fatihah in his own language.<br>
D. Say phrases such as “Alhamdulillāh, Allāhu Akbar, lā ilāha illā Allāh” repeatedly.</p>

<p>4.  سُبْحَانَ رَبِّيَ الْعَظِيمِ is the supplication that the Prophet ﷺ used to say in<br>
