<h3>Question 3</h3>
<p>Read the story and answer all the questions below.</p>

<p>Yusuf had just transferred to a new school. On his first day, he walked into his class and noticed that only two empty seats were left at the back of the classroom.</p>

<p>One of the seats was next to Haris. Haris was funny, loud, and very popular. He spent most of the lesson whispering jokes and making memes about teachers in the class WhatsApp group. Everyone laughed with him, but sometimes his jokes were rude and hurtful.</p>

<p>The other seat was next to Luqman. Luqman was quiet but kind. He greeted Yusuf the moment he entered, moved his books to make space, and offered to share his notes. During breaks, Luqman often went to the musolla for Dhuha peryer with a small group of students and reminded them, “Come, let’s pray together before we eat.”</p>

<p>At recess, Haris called out, “Yusuf, sit here! We’re watching videos—this one is so tuff!” On the other side of the canteen, Luqman waved to him and said, “Yusuf, after you eat, want to come with us to the musolla? I’ll show you around the school.”</p>

<p>On his way home that day, Yusuf remembered something his teacher once taught from a hadith: that a person follows the religion of his close friend, and that a good friend is like a musk seller while a bad friend is like a bellow blower. He thought about why people usually become friends (same class, same jokes, same games) and then he remembered that Islam teaches friendship should be intentional, not just accidental.</p>

<p>That night, Yusuf made du‘a: “O Allah, give me friends who help me get closer to You.” The next day, when he entered the classroom, both empty seats were still there. He paused for a moment, took a deep breath, and walked towards Luqman’s desk.</p>

<p>1. Is choosing our friends important in Islam? Explain your answer with two reasons and two examples.<br>
_________________________________________________________________________<br>
(4 marks)</p>

<p>2. Based on the story, how should Yusuf treat Luqman and Haris according to Islamic teachings? Explain the difference between how he should deals with each of them.<br>
_________________________________________________________________________<br>
(4 marks)</p>

<p>3. If a person cannot find a good friend around them, what should they do according to the Islamic guidance on friendship?<br>
_________________________________________________________________________<br>
(3 marks)</p>

<p>4. What are the main qualities and characteristics of a good friend in Islam?<br>
_________________________________________________________________________<br>
(4 marks)</p>

